In this article, President Trump discusses various topics, including trade with China, tax reform, political correctness on college campuses, and the opioid epidemic. He addresses concerns about China stealing jobs and the need for fair trade. Trump also emphasizes the positive impact of tax cuts, particularly for the middle class and millennials. He expresses his support for free speech on college campuses and the need to fight against political correctness. Trump mentions his administration's efforts to combat the opioid crisis, including allocating $6 billion and developing less addictive painkillers. He also advocates for tougher penalties for drug dealers.